  2. covariance among ancestry segments
load("~/git/hemostat/copdgene/arm_chr1.rdata") # -> `arm`
load("~/git/hemostat/copdgene/cov_acs_chr1.rdata") # -> `cov_acs`

2.2 Individual covariance (ARM)

3 Model with two random effects: center and ancestry

Fitted to all ind.

mod1 <- relmatLmer(FEV1_FVC_utah ~ Age_Enroll + Age_Enroll2 + gender + 
  SmokCigNow + ATS_PackYears + acs_global + (1 | ccenter), phen)

Fitted to the first 200 ind.:

mod2 <- relmatLmer(FEV1_FVC_utah ~ Age_Enroll + Age_Enroll2 + gender + 
  SmokCigNow + ATS_PackYears + acs_global + (1 | ccenter) + (1|sid), phen[1:200, ],
  relmat = list(sid = arm))
vf <- as.data.frame(VarCorr(mod2))[, c("grp", "vcov")]
vf$prop <- with(vf, vcov / sum(vcov))

vf 
       grp        vcov       prop
1      sid 0.006787867 0.25084512
2  ccenter 0.001795253 0.06634344
3 Residual 0.018476871 0.68281144
